measurements.description:
Three nicely spaced flowers on one 5.2 cm inflorescence, originating from the base of a pseudobulb, and three buds on 

	one immature inflorescence; three fans of seven to eight leaves, largest leaf 2.9 cm x 63 cm, three ovate leafless 

	backbulbs 13 cm X 14 cm, grown in bark in 15-cm plastic pot; flower white; sepals light pink cast, tiny dark pink speckles

	proximally; petals short red line mid-rib distally; lip dark burgundy splotches throughout, overlaid yellow centrally, 

	callus yellow, dark burgundy splotches; column white, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte; 

	reference www.holalanvietnam.org, Hoi Hoa Lan Viet Nam Cymbidium sanderae by Dang Buiafer plant ID; origin Vietnam; 

	awarded for color of white with attractively patterned dark burgundy spots; this should invalidate award 20194134, 

	which was awarded to a Cymbidium parishii.
